<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/5–1848.: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Durbrow</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-18">May 18,
                                1948</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>937. Soviet press May 18 carried texts of note Foreign Minister of Israel
                            Shertok requesting Soviet recognition Israel and Molotov’s note
                            conveying Soviet Government’s affirmative decision.</p>
                        <p>Department pass Jerusalem 10.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Durbrow</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>